1. There are 2 axis: a) Main axis b) Cross axis. By default, horizontal line is the main axis
   and vertical line is the cross axis.

Each containers can be arranges across the main axis or the cross axis (as required) using the
following properties:

CONTAINER PROPERTIES - To arrange the containers across the main or cross axis

1. flex-direction: row | row-reverse | column | column-reverse
2. flex-wrap: nowrap | wrap | wrap-reverse
3. justify-content: flex-start | flex-end | center | space-between | space-around | space-evenly

- justify-content is for alignment of the containers across the main axis

4. align-items: stretch | flex-start | flex-end | center | baseline

- align-items is to align the containers across the cross axis.

5. align-content: stretch | flex-start | flex-end | center | space-between | space-around

- align-content is to align the items within the container

ITEM PROPERTIES - To arrange the items

1. align-self: auto | stretch | flex-start | flex-end | center | baseline
2. order: 0 | <integer>
3. flex-grow: 0 | <integer>
4. flex-shrink: 1 | <integer>
5. flex-basic: auto | <length>

- property 3, 4 and 5 can be combined as flex: 0 1 auto.

\*\* svg fonts are much better than icon fonts because they can be treated as text and also easy for screen assistance devices. https://icomoon.io/app/#/select website can be used to download svg
